The paper deals with image-to-image transformation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new objective function for GANs, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which involves graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM) research.
